cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a control system to manage traffic congestion in a network of interconnected roads. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper develops a model predictive boundary control and a receding horizon optimizer to optimize traffic flows at the NOIR boundary nodes and intersections, respectively. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a physics-based approach to model traffic coordination and proposes an interactive control system to manage traffic congestion. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): Although the paper does not explicitly mention robotics, the proposed control system can be seen as a form of traffic automation. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses simulation to model traffic congestion in a heterogeneous NOIR and evaluate the effectiveness of the proposed interactive control system.
